OL,3,C'Climate Whiplash' puts world's
OL,4,Cbiggest cities at risk of drought and
OL,5,Cflooding
OL,7,FColombo in Sri Lanka is seeing the
OL,8,Fmost dramatic shift to more rainfall.
OL,10,FWhilst Cairo in Egypt is drying
OL,11,Ffastest.
OL,13,F17% of cities, including Jakarta in
OL,14,FIndonesia, are experiencing what's
OL,15,Fcalled a 'climate whiplash,' where
OL,16,Fthey swing from extreme wet to extreme
OL,17,Fdry.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
