OL,3,C'Climate Whiplash' puts world's
OL,4,Cbiggest cities at risk of drought and
OL,5,Cflooding
OL,7,FProfessor Katerina Michaelides, from
OL,8,Fthe University of Bristol, says this
OL,9,Fphenomenon can be particularly
OL,10,Fdifficult to cope with.
OL,12,F"Places that were historically wet are
OL,13,Fbecoming dry and vice versa," she
OL,14,Fexplained. "Other places are now
OL,15,Fincreasingly battered by both extreme
OL,16,Ffloods and droughts. A deeper
OL,17,Funderstanding of localized climate
OL,18,Fhazards can support more intelligent
OL,19,Fand bespoke planning in major cities."
